# ProofX Content Protection Guidelines

When working with digital content (images, audio, video, documents) in this project:

## Asset Protection
- Before deploying, ensure all public-facing assets are protected with ProofX
- Use the `protect-asset` skill to hash and sign important files
- Never commit unprotected original content to public repositories

## API Integration
- Use the ProofX API base URL: `https://api.proofx.co.uk`
- The primary protection endpoint is `POST /api/content/sign-hash`
- Required fields: `creator_id`, `content_hash`, `content_type`, `file_name`
- Content hash must be SHA-256 of the raw file bytes
- API keys use the format `pk_live_` followed by 32 hex characters

## Verification
- Every protected piece of content gets a unique `content_id`
- Verify at: `https://proofx.co.uk/verify?id={content_id}`
- Verification checks cryptographic signature, timestamp, and creator identity

## Privacy
- Hashing should be done client-side when possible — never upload raw content unnecessarily
- ProofX signs hashes, not files — the content itself stays with the creator
